article.headline: Cal St.-Fullerton 106, San Diego Christian 60
article.story: FULLERTON, Calif. -- Jared Brandon had 16 points, Marquise Horne recorded a double-double with 15 points and 10 rebounds and Cal State-Fullerton sprinted past NAIA San Diego Christian 106-60 on Friday night. The Titans had five other players in double figures with Sammy Yeager and D.J. Seeley with 15 points apiece. Kwame Vaughn had 12 points while Deuce Johnson and Alex Harris each chipped in with 10. Cal State-Fullerton (3-2) couldn't miss in the first half, shooting an impressive 64.5 percent by making 20 of 31 shots and drained nine 3-pointers. San Diego Christian called a timeout after Raphael Rodriguez hit a 3-pointer at the 15:50 mark to cut the Titans lead down to two at 11-9, but the move back fired and Cal State-Fullerton went on a 45-22 run to close out the first half and take a 56-32 lead at the break. The Titans scored 30 points off 19 Hawks turnovers.
